## 🔴 Crash Bugs (3)

### 1. Bare [log()](file:///f:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/2.Script_Split_Chapter/core/api_client.py#63-83) called before lambda definition

| Pipeline | Line | Code |
|---|---|---|
| Narrative | 1543 | [log("No chapters selected")](file:///f:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/2.Script_Split_Chapter/core/api_client.py#63-83) |
| Narrative | 1564 | [log("✗ No frameworks found...")](file:///f:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/2.Script_Split_Chapter/core/api_client.py#63-83) |
| Review | 2086 | [log("No chapters selected")](file:///f:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/2.Script_Split_Chapter/core/api_client.py#63-83) |
| Review | 2106 | [log("✗ No frameworks found...")](file:///f:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/2.Script_Split_Chapter/core/api_client.py#63-83) |

**Problem**: [log](file:///f:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/2.Script_Split_Chapter/core/api_client.py#63-83) is defined as a lambda inside [_run()](file:///f:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/2.Script_Split_Chapter/ui/rewrite_style_tab.py#2125-2914) (lines 1598, 2139). But these lines are OUTSIDE [_run()](file:///f:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/2.Script_Split_Chapter/ui/rewrite_style_tab.py#2125-2914) — they're in the parent method body where [log](file:///f:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/2.Script_Split_Chapter/core/api_client.py#63-83) is not defined. If checked is empty or frameworks missing → **NameError: name 'log' is not defined**.

**Fix**: Replace with `self._log.log(...)`.

---

### 2. `self._stop_flag = False` reset in [_run()](file:///f:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/2.Script_Split_Chapter/ui/rewrite_style_tab.py#2125-2914) causes race condition

| Pipeline | Line |
|---|---|
| Narrative | 1590 |
| Review | 2131 |

**Problem**: When multiple jobs run in parallel, each [_run()](file:///f:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/2.Script_Split_Chapter/ui/rewrite_style_tab.py#2125-2914) resets `self._stop_flag = False` on entry. If user clicks Stop for job 1 (sets `_stop_flag = True`), and job 2 starts after → it resets `_stop_flag = False`, accidentally un-stopping job 1.

**Impact**: Low — per-job `stop_event` already handles this correctly. `_stop_flag` is "legacy compat" (line 59). But still incorrect.

**Fix**: Remove or guard with `if not stop_event:`.

---

### 3. `self._running = True` shared across parallel jobs

| Line | Code |
|---|---|
| 1570, 2112 | `self._running = True` |
| 2913 (finally) | `self._running = False` |

**Problem**: If 3 jobs run in parallel, the first to finish sets `self._running = False` while 2 others still running.

**Impact**: Low if nothing checks `self._running`. Currently only used for UI state → could cause "Rewrite" button to re-enable prematurely.

**Fix**: Count active jobs instead of boolean flag.

